Rating: 4
Made some changes and it was amazing! First, I cut the potatoes into bite sized pieces. Second, I sliced and minced the garlic. Third, I added the capers to the mix and baked everything together. It turned out so good. I cooked longer than suggested to get a crispy golden brown on the potatoes. The purple and red potatoes are expensive, but well worth it.

Rating: 2
I agree with reviewers who found the potates dry. I used a mix of baby yukon, red and purple potatoes and found all but the yukons dry and flavorless. At $4 a bag, I'll skip these next time and use regular yukons cut into bite sized pieces. I had problems with the fresh rosemary. It became very dry and lost flavor. I'll try dried next time, which seems to hold up better in the oven. In my haste to get dinner out of the oven on onto the table, I forgot to add the capers until after the potatoes were out of the oven. Will definitely try these again and get this part right. I second the reviewer who suggested larger capers so they don't become lost on the plate.

