It's already too hot to use the oven for dinner, so I tried a pan roast. I microwaved the potatoes on high until they were just tender, then popped them into a dry cast iron skillet on high heat to add some color. Added olive oil, garlic, salt, and rosemary after a toasty brown crust developed, and cooked until nicely fragrant. Hubby loved 'em, even though I forgot to add the capers. Looking forward to making these in the oven come fall.

